    <text id="A9515T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Trout requests information about McFarland's slave, Rhoda, who is linked to the
                    possible theft of bacon by other slaves in Staunton.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1863-10-05">Oct 5, 1863</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Doctor McFarland, <lb/>
                        <abbr expan="Dear">D</abbr>Sir:</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>We have much stealing of bacon &amp;c in town - this morning a negro woman
                    has been arrested with a <orig reg="piece">peice</orig> of bacon in her
                    possession which appears to have been <hi rend="underline">in oats</hi> - which
                        <hi rend="underline">she says</hi> she got from your negro woman <orig
                        reg="Rhoda">
                        <hi rend="underline">Roby</hi>
                    </orig> - through the hands of another slave; the woman is in possession of the
                    military in the guard house, and I address you this note as your woman is
                    implicated, that you may <pb n="2"/> investigate the matter - and if she is
                    guilty that she may be properly punished. Robberies of meat houses occur here
                    nearly every night &amp; we must do something to arrest the perpetrators. If
                    your woman is innocent we must have her as a witness.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours very truly,</salute>
                    <signed>N. K. Trout</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
